radiographic_examinations.findings: Minimal dependent atelectasis; diffuse hypoattenuation of the liver consistent with fatty infiltration; diffuse fat stranding associated with the head of the pancreas; minimal thickening of the left Gerota's fascia; no fluid collection; no intra-abdominal fluid collection, ascites, pneumoperitoneum; normal appearance of kidney, gallbladder, adrenal glands, spleen, stomach, duodenum, and bowel; normal pelvic organs.
